# ─── Required by main.go (multi-issuer resource server) ──────────────

# Comma-separated list of trusted Signet issuer URLs. Each one must
# match the `iss` claim of tokens it signs and the `issuer` field of its
# OIDC discovery document, byte-for-byte.
#
# Use cases:
#   - Multi-region: one Signet per region.
#   - Multi-domain: one Signet per domain under a shared API.
#   - Migration:    keep both old + new Signet during cutover.
#   - Federation:   trust a partner organization's Signet.
TRUSTED_ISSUERS=https://auth-a.example.com,https://auth-b.example.com

# Required `aud` claim value, applied to ALL trusted issuers. Must be set
# unless SKIP_AUDIENCE_CHECK=1. If your issuers emit different `aud`
# values per issuer, see the README for the per-issuer extension.
EXPECTED_AUDIENCE=

# Set to 1 to explicitly disable `aud` enforcement — only for issuers
# that don't emit `aud` on access tokens. Accepting any audience means
# any holder of a valid token can call this API.
SKIP_AUDIENCE_CHECK=0

# ─── Optional: cross-domain defense for short domain codes ───────────
# Map: which `domain` codes is each issuer permitted to sign for?
# Format:  iss1=domainA,domainB;iss2=domainC,domainD
# Domain values are lower-cased before comparison.
#
# When set, every issuer in TRUSTED_ISSUERS MUST appear here (with at
# least one domain) — a missing entry is a startup error so a typo never
# silently disables the check for one issuer.
#
# When unset, the cross-domain check is skipped (any trusted issuer may
# sign a token for any domain). Strongly recommended for production
# multi-domain deployments where domain values are short codes like
# "oa" / "hwrd" / "swrd" with no DNS-style trust boundary.
ISSUER_DOMAINS=https://auth-a.example.com=oa,hwrd;https://auth-b.example.com=swrd,cdomain

# ─── Optional: Signet private-claim prefix override ────────────────
# Overrides the Signet server's JWT_PRIVATE_CLAIM_PREFIX (default
# "extra"), applied uniformly to every entry in TRUSTED_ISSUERS — so
# all issuers in this MultiVerifier must share the same prefix. If your
# fleet runs different prefixes per issuer, build one Verifier per
# prefix and dispatch yourself. Leave blank for the SDK default.
JWT_PRIVATE_CLAIM_PREFIX=
